x1d h29 y772 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Preserve </div><div class="t m2 xa8 h29 y773 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m34d x5b h29 y772 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Flavor </div><div class="t m48e x22 h15 y774 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The savor of the salt represents the vital power of the Christian—</div><div class="t m5b0 x4e h15 y775 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the love of Jesus in the heart, the righteousness of Christ pervading </div><div class="t m485 x4e h15 y1b0 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the life. . . . </div><div class="t m5b1 x22 h15 y65 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Unless the Holy Spirit can use us as agents through whom to </div><div class="t m39a x4e h15 y776 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">communicate to the world the truth as it is in Jesus, we are as salt that </div><div class="t m44b x4e h15 y333 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">has lost its savor and is entirely worthless.&quot;—Thoughts </div><div class="t m131 x5b h15 y333 ff6 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">from the Mount </div><div class="t m1e0 x4e h15 y1b2 ff6 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of Blessing, </div><div class="t m16c x45 h15 y1b2 ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pp. 36, 37. </div><div class="t m130 x55 h29 y777 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How do we become the salt of the earth? Acts 4:13. </div><div class="t m5b2 x4d h29 y283 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">To be an effective flavoring agent, salt must be thoroughly </div><div class="t m5b3 x3d h29 y284 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mixed with food. What does this tell us about how we should live </div><div class="t m11b x65 h29 y148 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as Christians? Does it conflict with the concept of being in the </div><div class="t m565 x65 h29 y285 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">world but not of the world? Explain. How can we mingle with </div><div class="t m5b x65 h29 y286 ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">others in order to fulfill our global mission without being nega-</div><div class="t m335 x65 h29 y33a ff4 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tively affected? </div><div cla